lmon is cooked quickly under a high heat broiler on a sheet pan with cherry tomatoes for an easy 20 minute recipe!","breadcrumb":{"@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#breadcrumb"},"inLanguage":"en-US","potentialAction":[{"@type":"ReadAction","target":["https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/"]}]},{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#primaryimage","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/tandoori-salmon-square.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/tandoori-salmon-square.jpg","width":1200,"height":1200,"caption":"Square photo of tandoori salmon filets on a sheet pan with burst cherry tomatoes."},{"@type":"BreadcrumbList","@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#breadcrumb","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Quick and Easy Recipes","item":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/category\/quick-and-easy\/"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"Sheet Pan Tandoori Salmon with Burst Cherry Tomatoes"}]},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/#website","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/","name":"Bowl of Delicious","description":"Real Food for Busy People","publisher":{"@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/#organization"},"potentialAction":[{"@type":"SearchAction","target":{"@type":"EntryPoint","urlTemplate":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/?s={search_term_string}"},"query-input":{"@type":"PropertyValueSpecification","valueRequired":true,"valueName":"search_term_string"}}],"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Organization","@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/#organization","name":"Bowl of Delicious","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","inLanguage":"en-US","@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/#\/schema\/logo\/image\/","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/alternate-logo-square-cropped-yoast.jpg","contentUrl":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/alternate-logo-square-cropped-yoast.jpg","width":400,"height":400,"caption":"Bowl of Delicious"},"image":{"@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/#\/schema\/logo\/image\/"},"sameAs":["http:\/\/www.facebook.com\/bowlofdelicious","https:\/\/x.com\/bowlofdelicious","http:\/\/www.instagram.com\/bowlofdelicious","https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/in\/elizabeth-lindemann-3a3a0b8","http:\/\/www.pinterest.com\/bowlofdelicious"]},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/#\/schema\/person\/f38c2237f9d2c84b32adef57801f043d","name":"Elizabeth Lindemann","description":"Hi, I'm Elizabeth! I create easy, real food recipes for busy people. I'm a former high school art teacher from New England, now full time food blogger near Austin, TX, where I live with my hubby and two baby girls, Zoey and Eleanor.","sameAs":["https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/about","https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/bowlofdelicious\/","https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/bowlofdelicious","https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/in\/elizabeth-lindemann-3a3a0b8\/","https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\/bowlofdelicious","https:\/\/x.com\/bowlofdelicious"],"url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/author\/evetlingmail-com\/"},{"@type":"Recipe","name":"Sheet Pan Tandoori Salmon with Burst Cherry Tomatoes","author":{"@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/#\/schema\/person\/f38c2237f9d2c84b32adef57801f043d"},"description":"A broiler is a great substitute for a tandoor in this tandoori salmon recipe due to its high heat. Salmon, coated in a tandoori spiced yogurt mixture, and cherry tomatoes with garlic are cooked for only about 10 minutes under the broiler, resulting in a gorgeous char on both the fish and vegetables.","datePublished":"2025-05-27T12:53:10+00:00","image":["https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/tandoori-salmon-square.jpg","https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/tandoori-salmon-square-500x500.jpg","https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/tandoori-salmon-square-500x375.jpg","https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/tandoori-salmon-square-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["4","4 servings"],"prepTime":"PT10M","cookTime":"PT10M","totalTime":"PT20M","recipeIngredient":["4  salmon filets (about 6 oz. each, preferably with the skin removed, see notes)","½ cup plain Greek yogurt (preferably full-fat)","2 tablespoons olive oil","2-3 tablespoons tandoori masala (see notes)","1 teaspoon kosher salt","3 cups cherry tomatoes","4 cloves garlic (roughly chopped)","2 tablespoons olive oil","1 teaspoon kosher salt","½ cup fresh chopped cilantro","lemon wedges (for serving, optional)","pickled red onions (for serving, optional (see notes))","naan bread or rice (for serving, optional)"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In the bottom of a shallow container or bowl big enough to fit the salmon, mix together the ½ cup plain Greek yogurt, 2 tablespoons olive oil, 2-3 tablespoons tandoori masala, and 1 teaspoon kosher salt. Then, add the 4 salmon filets and flip around to coat, using a spoon or spatula (or you hands) if necessary to get a nice thick even coating. Cover and place in your fridge for 1-6 hours (if you&#39;re short on time you can skip this - see notes! This is a great time to make your pickled red onions if using - see notes for more on this as well!).","name":"In the bottom of a shallow container or bowl big enough to fit the salmon, mix together the ½ cup plain Greek yogurt, 2 tablespoons olive oil, 2-3 tablespoons tandoori masala, and 1 teaspoon kosher salt. Then, add the 4 salmon filets and flip around to coat, using a spoon or spatula (or you hands) if necessary to get a nice thick even coating. Cover and place in your fridge for 1-6 hours (if you&#39;re short on time you can skip this - see notes! This is a great time to make your pickled red onions if using - see notes for more on this as well!).","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#wprm-recipe-28991-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"When you&#39;re ready to cook, preheat your broiler and place the top oven rack 8-10 inches away from it.","name":"When you&#39;re ready to cook, preheat your broiler and place the top oven rack 8-10 inches away from it.","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#wprm-recipe-28991-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"In a medium bowl, mix together the 3 cups cherry tomatoes, roughly chopped 4 cloves garlic, 2 tablespoons olive oil, and 1 teaspoon kosher salt. Dump onto a sheet pan and spread out evenly around the edges of the sheet pan, leaving the center empty (but still coated in oil from the tomato mix).","name":"In a medium bowl, mix together the 3 cups cherry tomatoes, roughly chopped 4 cloves garlic, 2 tablespoons olive oil, and 1 teaspoon kosher salt. Dump onto a sheet pan and spread out evenly around the edges of the sheet pan, leaving the center empty (but still coated in oil from the tomato mix).","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#wprm-recipe-28991-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the marinated filets of salmon to the center of the sheet pan. Use a spatula or spoon to get any excess yogurt mixture and spread evenly on top of the salmon pieces.","name":"Add the marinated filets of salmon to the center of the sheet pan. Use a spatula or spoon to get any excess yogurt mixture and spread evenly on top of the salmon pieces.","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#wprm-recipe-28991-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the sheet pan on the top rack under the broiler. This is important: WATCH IT CAREFULLY! Your broiler may be stronger or weaker depending on whether you have gas or electric. It will need about 10 minutes of cooking time total, and you should take it out when the salmon reaches an internal temperature of 125-130 degrees F (see notes). The tomatoes will burst and get blackened a bit on top, and the top of the salmon should char nicely and evenly. If it&#39;s all nice and charred but the salmon isn&#39;t fully cooked, just move the sheet pan to the bottom rack away from the direct heat for the remainder of the cooking time until the salmon is fully cooked.","name":"Place the sheet pan on the top rack under the broiler. This is important: WATCH IT CAREFULLY! Your broiler may be stronger or weaker depending on whether you have gas or electric. It will need about 10 minutes of cooking time total, and you should take it out when the salmon reaches an internal temperature of 125-130 degrees F (see notes). The tomatoes will burst and get blackened a bit on top, and the top of the salmon should char nicely and evenly. If it&#39;s all nice and charred but the salmon isn&#39;t fully cooked, just move the sheet pan to the bottom rack away from the direct heat for the remainder of the cooking time until the salmon is fully cooked.","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#wprm-recipe-28991-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Remove from the oven and sprinkle everything evenly with the ½ cup fresh chopped cilantro. Serve with lemon wedges for squeezing, pickled red onions, and naan bread or rice if desired.","name":"Remove from the oven and sprinkle everything evenly with the ½ cup fresh chopped cilantro. Serve with lemon wedges for squeezing, pickled red onions, and naan bread or rice if desired.","url":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#wprm-recipe-28991-step-0-5"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"5","ratingCount":"1","reviewCount":"1"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This was super easy and absolutely delicious! I will definitely be adding it to the dinner rotation.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Victoria"},"datePublished":"2025-06-14"}],"recipeCategory":["Dinner"],"recipeCuisine":["Indian"],"keywords":"Broiled Salmon, salmon and tomatoes, sheet pan salmon, tandoori salmon","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"416 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"9 g","proteinContent":"38 g","fatContent":"25 g","saturatedFatContent":"4 g","transFatContent":"0.003 g","cholesterolContent":"95 mg","sodiumContent":"1262 mg","fiberContent":"1 g","sugarContent":"4 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"20 g","servingSize":"1 serving"},"@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\/\/www.bowlofdelicious.com\/tandoori-salmon\/"}]}</script>
	<!-- / Yoast SEO Premium plugin. -->


